<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-12-20T09:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-12-20T09:35:00-05:00" n="613" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d613">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363 Standard Oil/318½:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Teheran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gotlieb</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-12-20T18:00:00+03:25"><hi rend="italic">December 20,
                                        1923—6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received December 20—4:28
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>This afternoon I officially witnessed signing of north Persian oil
                            concession by Reza Khan, Prime Minister, and R. Soper representing
                            Sinclair Exploration Company. I shall send text as soon as possible.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gotlieb</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>